						               													<description>In Bukiet, players grow flowers on their personal sheets. The dice symbolize customers who want to buy certain types of flowers. Players cut flowers in their fields to make bouquets for their customers to score points, but each flower can be cut only once, so try to keep your customers happy! You have several ways to win. Become the best flower grower!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In more detail, the game is divided into rounds, and at the start of a round the active player throws all six dice. Starting from the first player, in clockwise direction, each player chooses one customer and encircles flowers in the correct color on their personal sheet. This means that the flowers have been cut from the player's field. When all players have chosen one die, the round ends, then the player on the left of the active player begins the next round. The game ends when at the end of the round a player has:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Cut all flowers in three colors, or&amp;#10;    Cut all flowers in four of the six fields.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You can score bonus points if you have the fewest unhappy customers. The player with the most points wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
